{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"300555-haru","title":"Haru","description":"Meet Haru, who loves to eat, run and\r\nplay. Even though there are nights when\r\nit’s hard to find a warm place to sleep, or\r\ndays when there isn’t enough food to eat,\r\nHaru is always certain that tomorrow will\r\nbe better. After all, as long as there is love\r\nand joy, it’s not a bad life!","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"3","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Manjari Chakravarti"],"illustrators":["Manjari Chakravarti"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Pratham Books","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/300555-haru"},"cover":{"card":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/703490/size3/b97ed02bce11100313314b0ad73e7bff.jpg","large":"https://static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/703490/size6/b97ed02bce11100313314b0ad73e7bff.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387638/size6/e05d748658cc6a1368c97d88a264739f.jpg","text":"2/15","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387686/size6/4e912ef236491294085403205e6c9d90.jpg","text":"Hi, I’m Haru!","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387687/size6/4652b14d4cc33f13f1758ee8e4b0a4e3.jpg","text":"This is where I spend most\nmornings.\nMy favourite breakfast is spicy chickpea curry, buttered toast with sugar on top, and sweet, milky tea.","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387688/size6/b62ef71256a419e9cd488a696b48163d.jpg","text":"On hot days,\nI can find shade.","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387690/size6/fd240ab2f10820f36b3dee574948a5c0.jpg","text":"On rainy days, shelter.","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387691/size6/4f0575045f91fae9ceaaf3547fb07504.jpg","text":"On cold nights, warmth.","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387692/size6/c2176cb14966e28c867bc2dd8bbbe72d.jpg","text":"One day, I got hurt on the busy road.","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387693/size6/b1b4df26613243fcba5ab37de24df137.jpg","text":"Dida found me.","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387695/size6/23f6ab7758af503785c06040573685dd.jpg","text":"She took me home.","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387696/size6/075f7a289ebf64da82f873fbeb9599a0.jpg","text":"She took care of me.\nShe fed me vegetables and fruit.","words":null},{"n":11,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387698/size6/16d72abf901a13b59ed4a4fb4f4eb748.jpg","text":"My new family is nice.\nThe boys are in trouble today so Dida is making them knit scarves.","words":null},{"n":12,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387699/size6/583ee57be622081044c788722d6ab5e4.jpg","text":"My leg is fine now.\nHere I am, helping with the laundry.","words":null},{"n":13,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387700/size6/a0614b1832e16eb74f7d20f793529bae.jpg","text":"Itʼs not a bad life.","words":null},{"n":14,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/387701/size6/3894f3f5c14bc3834269efce46cf9567.jpg","text":"Haru was a real goat!\nHe was rescued by Granny Ituko in\nSantiniketan in West Bengal, during the 1970s. He grew up as a member of her family, along with many dogs, birds, cows, squirrels, pigeons and ducks, and one\nsnake.\nGoats are intelligent and funny, and they come running when called, especially if you learn to bleat like them — which I did. They can be really mischievous, they chew on almost everything, they get into all sorts of trouble!\nThis is how I imagine Haru’s life was.","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":14,"words":194}}